WEBVTT

00:01.435 --> 00:03.504
[ Horns honking ]

00:08.542 --> 00:12.613
We're on our next stop around
the world in India,

00:12.646 --> 00:16.150
and we're in a...rickshaw.

00:16.184 --> 00:19.053
* Who are they
tryin' to assimilate *

00:19.087 --> 00:21.655
* Every winter,
Bombay assimilate the glare *

00:21.689 --> 00:24.125
* It feel like fire...

00:24.158 --> 00:27.428
From the outside, India
may seem like a paradox.

00:27.461 --> 00:30.098
It's one of the few cultures
in the world

00:30.131 --> 00:33.634
that can trace its roots to the
beginning of recorded history,

00:33.667 --> 00:35.569
but it's also a new country,

00:35.603 --> 00:38.506
celebrating only 70 years
of independence.

00:38.539 --> 00:40.841
* I'm in Bombay,
dancing to a banger *

00:40.874 --> 00:44.112
* Listenin' to Biggie,
ain't nobody with a banger *

00:44.145 --> 00:47.515
With a billion people
and 22 official languages,

00:47.548 --> 00:51.252
there are countless differences
between regions.

00:51.285 --> 00:52.586
But what unites Indians

00:52.620 --> 00:54.788
is the spirituality
of Eastern religions

00:54.822 --> 00:57.525
and the legacy of British
colonial rule.

00:57.558 --> 01:00.361
* I'm on the beat like a beast
with a temper *

01:00.394 --> 01:02.696
It's this duality
that allows Indian law

01:02.730 --> 01:05.633
to recognize a third gender,

01:05.666 --> 01:08.336
but also stigmatize
homosexuality.

01:08.369 --> 01:11.539
So we want to learn more

01:11.572 --> 01:14.575
about the LGBTQ experience
here in India.

01:14.608 --> 01:17.178
* Hey, Savage, ask me,
it's madness *

01:17.211 --> 01:19.547
* Humans is humans
who care who they smashing *

01:19.580 --> 01:22.216
Both: "Gaycation: India."

01:22.250 --> 01:26.454
**

01:26.487 --> 01:28.689
