07:33.521 --> 07:36.089
**

07:44.732 --> 07:46.199
Tell me, from
your point of view,

07:46.233 --> 07:48.235
what it's like to be gay
and live in Bombay.

07:48.268 --> 07:49.937
Man #2: You do find
homophobic people,

07:49.970 --> 07:52.540
but if we actually compared
the scenario in India,

07:52.573 --> 07:54.141
Bombay's quite a cool place

07:54.174 --> 07:56.243
because you have safer space,
party every Saturday.

07:56.276 --> 07:58.178
And you feel -- you feel
totally comfortable

07:58.211 --> 07:59.913
just being out
and being proud, yeah?

07:59.947 --> 08:01.081
-Pretty much.
-Very much.

08:01.114 --> 08:02.850
Love that.
So, are you a couple?

08:02.883 --> 08:04.117
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

08:04.151 --> 08:06.086
Wow, the first couple
I've seen tonight.

08:06.119 --> 08:07.855
You're out, yeah?
-Oh, yeah. Very.

08:07.888 --> 08:09.623
You're open about
your sexuality,

08:09.657 --> 08:11.224
and you're open about being
a couple out in public?

08:11.258 --> 08:12.626
-Yeah.
-Can't help it.

08:12.660 --> 08:13.861
Can't help it?

08:13.894 --> 08:15.262
What do you mean
by you can't help it?

08:15.295 --> 08:17.865
It becomes fairly obvious
at times. [ Chuckles ]

08:17.898 --> 08:19.600
So the bottom line,
this party's,

08:19.633 --> 08:21.635
like, really important
to your expression,

08:21.669 --> 08:23.704
to your identity,
and to your future?

08:23.737 --> 08:26.640
I think it has given me
the courage to stand strong

08:26.674 --> 08:29.543
and be myself and say, "Yes,
I am a proud gay man,

08:29.577 --> 08:30.711
a homosexual man."

08:30.744 --> 08:32.680
-Right.
-All right. Thanks, guys.

08:32.713 --> 08:34.047
I'll leave you alone.
-See you, man.

08:34.081 --> 08:35.215
-But I'll see you in there.
-Thanks, man.

08:35.248 --> 08:36.850
-Nice meeting you.
-I'm sweaty.

08:36.884 --> 08:38.552
**

08:38.586 --> 08:42.055
Page: There seems to be a strong
community for gay men,

08:42.089 --> 08:44.324
at least under
the cover of night.

08:44.357 --> 08:46.927
What's life like
in the light of day?

08:46.960 --> 08:50.998
And we can't help but ask,
where are the women?

08:55.869 --> 08:59.106
**

08:59.139 --> 09:02.342
Page: India's known for the
tradition of arranged marriages.

09:02.375 --> 09:09.016
Even today, they still make up
88% of all marital unions here.

09:16.690 --> 09:18.926
Matchmaking apps
and social listings

09:18.959 --> 09:21.629
have modernized
the search for a partner,

09:21.662 --> 09:24.031
but it's the still
the imperative of the parent

09:24.064 --> 09:27.200
to make sure their child finds
an appropriate husband or wife.

09:27.234 --> 09:29.269
Article 377 in the books,

09:29.302 --> 09:32.706
marriage equality
isn't up for debate.

09:32.740 --> 09:35.175
But like any mother,
Padmav wanted her son

09:35.208 --> 09:37.611
to continue
in the family tradition,

09:37.645 --> 09:40.781
so she placed a matrimonial ad
in the local paper

09:40.814 --> 09:42.950
requesting a groom for her son.

09:42.983 --> 09:44.051
[ Doorbell rings ]

09:44.084 --> 09:45.686
-Oh, hi.
-Hi. [ Laughs ]

09:45.719 --> 09:46.720
-Hi.
-Hi. I'm Ian.

09:46.754 --> 09:47.955
Nice to meet you.
-Ellen.

09:47.988 --> 09:49.623
-Hi, Ellen.
-Pleasure to meet you.

09:49.657 --> 09:51.992
-Ian, nice to meet you.
-Wow.

09:52.025 --> 09:53.060
Page: Oh, you're pretty.

09:53.093 --> 09:54.261
-He's a gay cat.
-Oh, he is?

09:54.294 --> 09:56.797
-Both of them are gay.
-Okay.

09:56.830 --> 09:58.766
So, how many people
live here?

09:58.799 --> 10:02.302
My mother, my father,
my grandmom, my cats.

10:02.335 --> 10:04.705
So if my cats are
the next generation,

10:04.738 --> 10:06.039
we have around three generations
living here.

10:06.073 --> 10:07.274
Wow.

10:07.307 --> 10:09.176
That's how Indian
families have been.

10:09.209 --> 10:10.978
They'll take a big house,

10:11.011 --> 10:13.413
and all of them would live
together -- really close knit.

10:13.446 --> 10:16.316
So, far as the concept
of dating is very new.

10:16.349 --> 10:18.351
-Right.
-Because family --

10:18.385 --> 10:20.854
if you don't find a family
for yourself,

10:20.888 --> 10:22.122
we'll find one for you.

10:22.155 --> 10:23.924
So, and when they
find one for you,

10:23.957 --> 10:25.959
they will find somebody
from the same language,

10:25.993 --> 10:27.127
from the same caste.

10:27.160 --> 10:28.328
So how does -- how does love

10:28.361 --> 10:29.362
come in to play
in all of this?

10:29.396 --> 10:30.864
I wouldn't call it love.

10:30.898 --> 10:32.666
But, you know, staying together,

10:32.700 --> 10:35.435
you have to make a lot of
adjustments and compromises.

10:35.468 --> 10:37.871
I mean, well, I was
going to talk -- to talk

10:37.905 --> 10:39.172
about the ad you placed

10:39.206 --> 10:40.974
because you guys
caused quite a stir

10:41.008 --> 10:42.876
[chuckling] I suppose.
-[ Laughs ]

10:42.910 --> 10:45.345
Harish: My mother was very
worried, and she said that,

10:45.378 --> 10:48.916
"You're -- you're 36, and
you're going to be single.

10:48.949 --> 10:52.252
You're not finding a suitor
for yourself.

10:52.285 --> 10:54.722
This is it.
I'm going to find one for you."

10:54.755 --> 10:56.289
And then she asked.
"Can we put an ad in Grindr?

10:56.323 --> 10:58.125
Mm.

10:58.158 --> 11:00.427
I said, "Grindr people meet on
Grindr for something else."

11:00.460 --> 11:03.030
[ Laughs ]
It's called Grindr
for a reason.

11:03.063 --> 11:04.998
We were sitting on the bed
and we were laughing,

11:05.032 --> 11:06.266
and I said,
"Are you serious?"

11:06.299 --> 11:07.735
And she said, "Yeah.
We should put an ad."

11:07.768 --> 11:08.902
I said, "Okay."

11:08.936 --> 11:10.704
And so how has that
just been

11:10.738 --> 11:13.073
for your family or
with friends, you know?

11:13.106 --> 11:14.708
How has it been
for the family?

11:14.742 --> 11:16.343
Woman:
Suddenly, I became very famous.

11:16.376 --> 11:18.045
Like, they didn't
like to see me,

11:18.078 --> 11:20.047
and they said, "Why you have
to go and place that ad?"

11:20.080 --> 11:21.481
They weren't very happy.

11:21.514 --> 11:23.350
Was that something you were
thinking about, though,

11:23.383 --> 11:24.785
when you were making
that ad

11:24.818 --> 11:26.186
that this would be
a public deal, yeah?

11:26.219 --> 11:27.788
No, I never thought about it.

11:27.821 --> 11:29.056
You know, earlier on,
I was very introvert.

11:29.089 --> 11:30.457
I didn't want
to face the family.

11:30.490 --> 11:32.192
I didn't want people
calling me names,

11:32.225 --> 11:33.794
like, "Oh, you have a gay son."

11:33.827 --> 11:35.428
I wanted everything
to be a secret.

11:35.462 --> 11:38.165
Slowly, I came out.
I said, "No. Let them talk.

11:38.198 --> 11:40.267
I want to do good for my son."
-Mm.

11:40.300 --> 11:41.935
-So, what...
-So, did you meet anybody?

11:41.969 --> 11:43.737
Yeah. What was
the end result of that?
Yeah.

11:43.771 --> 11:47.074
So, we spoke to a few people,
it didn't work out.

11:47.107 --> 11:48.508
And I'm still single.

11:48.541 --> 11:51.178
And Ellen, possibly, you can
find me a nice suitor.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.312
I'm coming to the U.S.

11:52.345 --> 11:53.881
I'll keep my eyes peeled.

11:53.914 --> 11:55.515
-Keep your eyes open.
-What's your type?

11:55.548 --> 11:58.485
As long as he's vegetarian,
he's animal loving,

11:58.518 --> 12:00.754
he's willing
to accept my cats.

12:00.788 --> 12:03.390
I'm willing -- I'm -- I'm --
I'll love him to death then.

12:05.358 --> 12:07.227
Page: Well, they were
incredibly sweet,

12:07.260 --> 12:10.130
incredibly welcoming.

12:10.163 --> 12:12.766
Daniel: It seemed like
it was more important

12:12.800 --> 12:14.234
for him to get married

12:14.267 --> 12:16.870
than actually to fall in love
and not get married.

12:16.904 --> 12:18.038
I guess I've not experienced
someone saying that,

12:18.071 --> 12:19.306
but no judgment.

12:19.339 --> 12:20.974
I just thought
that was interesting.

12:21.008 --> 12:22.776
Looking at these things, they --
they stand out strongly.

12:22.810 --> 12:24.011
Mm-hmm.

12:24.044 --> 12:25.846
But when you reflect
on your own culture,

12:25.879 --> 12:28.515
you know, there's still stigma
when people don't get married.

12:28.548 --> 12:31.551
It can be easy to,
I think, not look at yourself

12:31.584 --> 12:34.387
or look at
where you come from.
Exactly.

12:34.421 --> 12:37.024
Page: If just choosing a partner
breaks social norms,

12:37.057 --> 12:40.493
then the LGBTQ community
must face a double stigma.

12:40.527 --> 12:43.363
To understand more of the issues
unique to India,

12:43.396 --> 12:44.898
we're meeting the person

12:44.932 --> 12:47.534
considered to be the grandfather
of the movement.

12:47.567 --> 12:49.937
-Thanks for having us.
-Pleasure.

12:49.970 --> 12:52.139
Page:
Ashok Row Kavi is the founder

12:52.172 --> 12:55.943
of one of India's first
LGBTQ organizations,

12:55.976 --> 12:57.344
The Humsafar Trust.

12:57.377 --> 12:59.880
Please don't shut down
the air-conditioning,

12:59.913 --> 13:01.048
