15:41.708 --> 15:43.710
I'd love to talk to you
about Gaysi

15:43.743 --> 15:45.645
and talk about
the organization.

15:45.678 --> 15:48.615
Yeah, so Gaysi started
in 2008 as a way

15:48.648 --> 15:51.351
to get Indian queer people
together

15:51.384 --> 15:53.720
to communicate
with each other.

15:53.753 --> 15:57.624
And now, we've started
doing events in Bombay,

15:57.657 --> 16:01.094
sort of to create safe spaces
for women mostly,

16:01.128 --> 16:02.562
than men to come
together

16:02.595 --> 16:04.998
because there's lots
of parties for men.

16:05.032 --> 16:06.766
There's lots of things
for men to do and...

16:06.799 --> 16:08.401
He knows.
Don't worry about it.

16:08.435 --> 16:10.270
So, you can...
-Show up to a gay party?

16:10.303 --> 16:12.072
...say whatever you want.

16:12.105 --> 16:13.173
Daniel: Yeah, I went to the Gay
Bombay party last night.

16:13.206 --> 16:14.607
How was that?

16:14.641 --> 16:16.209
It w-- I mean, it was a nice
time, but there --

16:16.243 --> 16:17.710
You know, there were
not women there.
Yep.

16:17.744 --> 16:20.247
Maybe you could give us a bit
of your individual stories

16:20.280 --> 16:23.283
of what it what means to be
a woman and queer in India.

16:23.316 --> 16:25.785
I think that more
than being a woman...

16:25.818 --> 16:28.255
[ Sighs ]
and then being queer is,

16:28.288 --> 16:30.790
you know, two layers
of stuff in India.

16:30.823 --> 16:32.359
Mm-hmm.

16:32.392 --> 16:34.694
I can speak for all three
of us in the sense

16:34.727 --> 16:38.065
that I think we come from a more
privileged background,

16:38.098 --> 16:40.300
so we have access...
-Mm-hmm.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.735
...and we're allowed
these safe spaces.

16:42.769 --> 16:45.772
But I think even then,
it's still, uh, difficult.

16:45.805 --> 16:49.042
You feel intimidated anyway
in a public space.

16:49.076 --> 16:54.581
I mean, you can be, and then --
It's just nice to have a place

16:54.614 --> 16:57.384
where people are not looking
at you and judging your...

16:57.417 --> 16:59.486
-Judge.
-...particular manner, you know?

16:59.519 --> 17:02.289
So that -- that is really
important, actually, I feel.

17:02.322 --> 17:05.125
Well, women in India aren't
allowed to have a sexuality...

17:05.158 --> 17:07.294
Yeah.
...whether you're
straight or not.

17:07.327 --> 17:09.562
Like, your job, as a woman,
is to have a womb,

17:09.596 --> 17:12.532
get married, produce a baby,
and that's it.
And that's it.

17:12.565 --> 17:17.804
The idea that you might even
want to have sex is alien.

17:17.837 --> 17:19.639
As a queer woman that means
you're associated

17:19.672 --> 17:21.408
by what happens
in your bedroom.
Yeah.

17:21.441 --> 17:22.775
That is just a part
of my identity.

17:22.809 --> 17:24.211
It doesn't define me.

17:30.583 --> 17:33.253
[ Bird squawks ]

17:33.286 --> 17:36.189
Page: Ian and I have been in
India for a couple of days now,

17:36.223 --> 17:38.291
and from the stories
we've been told,

17:38.325 --> 17:40.827
there seems to be a strong
patriarchal tradition.

17:40.860 --> 17:43.830
We want to hear from more
lesbian and bisexual women,

17:43.863 --> 17:46.533
because for them, just being
in a relationship

17:46.566 --> 17:48.235
challenges gender roles.

17:48.268 --> 17:50.803
Thanks for coming and thanks
for being part of this.

17:50.837 --> 17:52.639
Woman:
No, thank you very much.

17:52.672 --> 17:55.675
Clearly, there's
difficulty to doing it,

17:55.708 --> 17:57.310
so we appreciate it.

17:57.344 --> 17:59.779
Page: We're meeting a young
woman to find out

17:59.812 --> 18:02.115
how social pressures
often keep women

18:02.149 --> 18:04.117
from coming out
and speaking out.

18:04.151 --> 18:06.453
Maybe you can describe to us
what it means

18:06.486 --> 18:08.688
to be an independent woman
in India.

18:08.721 --> 18:10.857
Mm...
[ Exhales sharply ]

18:10.890 --> 18:12.225
It's not easy.

18:12.259 --> 18:13.626
For a woman, it's just like,

18:13.660 --> 18:15.595
"A," how can you leave
your house?

18:15.628 --> 18:17.497
"B," you have responsibilities.

18:17.530 --> 18:20.900
So all of that is ingrained in
them at a very, very young age.

18:20.933 --> 18:23.370
The son in the house,
goes to work, you know,

18:23.403 --> 18:24.871
go out and do whatever he wants,

18:24.904 --> 18:27.140
and stay out to whatever time
he wants,

18:27.174 --> 18:28.508
when that's absolutely okay.

18:28.541 --> 18:30.510
But God forbid the daughter
wants to do that.

18:30.543 --> 18:32.612
And God forbid the daughter's
not attracted to boys.

18:32.645 --> 18:33.713
-Yeah.
-My God.

18:33.746 --> 18:35.248
Yeah.
And so -- yeah.

18:35.282 --> 18:37.350
I think a lot of women
don't come out,

18:37.384 --> 18:39.152
and these are people

18:39.186 --> 18:41.821
who have totally different
feelings towards, you know,

18:41.854 --> 18:44.391
the opposite sex and have to,
like, live and marry

18:44.424 --> 18:45.692
and, you know, give them
children.

18:45.725 --> 18:47.260
It's absurd.

18:47.294 --> 18:48.661
And would you say the majority
of queer women

18:48.695 --> 18:50.330
in this country are
in that position?

18:50.363 --> 18:54.167
Yeah.
But, uh, I'm very, very lucky

18:54.201 --> 18:57.170
to have an extremely supportive
and understanding family.

18:57.204 --> 18:58.805
-Mm.
-Why is it that you're --

18:58.838 --> 19:01.208
You're doing this interview
anonymously?

19:01.241 --> 19:03.510
Well, I'm doing this interview
anonymously

19:03.543 --> 19:04.744
because of my partner.

19:04.777 --> 19:06.713
She comes from one
of the families

19:06.746 --> 19:08.781
that I've been talking
to you about.

19:08.815 --> 19:10.883
And, uh, let's just put it
this way,

19:10.917 --> 19:12.952
that it wouldn't go down
very well.

19:12.985 --> 19:14.621
What do you mean
by that?

19:14.654 --> 19:18.391
It -- It's over,
like, your life is over.
Mm-hmm.

19:18.425 --> 19:20.293
Like, believe me when I say
that your life is over.

19:20.327 --> 19:21.928
It means that you are locked in
the room till I get you married,

19:21.961 --> 19:23.396
and that's it.
-Mm-hmm.

19:23.430 --> 19:24.864
And you have no say
in the matter.

19:24.897 --> 19:26.366
She's actually been
my best friend for 10 years.

19:26.399 --> 19:27.800
-Mm-hmm.
-Mm-hmm.

19:27.834 --> 19:29.502
And I knew I loved her
from the day I met her,

19:29.536 --> 19:31.838
when, in 2005, when we were,
like, 15 years old.

19:31.871 --> 19:33.940
Well, it took me a year
to convince her,

19:33.973 --> 19:36.943
that we could date, because
her thing was, like, "I cannot,

19:36.976 --> 19:39.746
because you know the kind
of family that I come from."

19:39.779 --> 19:41.614
And I was like, "Okay,
I understand that,

19:41.648 --> 19:43.850
but I'm not asking you to marry
me right now, so I'm --

19:43.883 --> 19:46.353
I mean, I'm not understanding
what the apprehension is."

19:46.386 --> 19:47.754
And she's like, "No,
'cause I know

19:47.787 --> 19:49.422
where this is gonna go
eventually.

19:49.456 --> 19:51.258
You know, it's never gonna
happen in my family."

19:51.291 --> 19:52.759
How does that
make you feel?

19:52.792 --> 19:54.361
Wha-- What do you...?

19:54.394 --> 19:56.463
You do realize that I'm gonna
have to be there

19:56.496 --> 19:57.897
organizing her wedding, right?

19:57.930 --> 19:59.632
I don't mean that as a joke.

19:59.666 --> 20:01.468
Because you're -- Because
you're best friends, or --

20:01.501 --> 20:04.003
Uh, best friends
and so close to her family,

20:04.036 --> 20:07.006
and if I don't, it'll --
Questions will be raised.

20:07.039 --> 20:09.909
So, basically, I'm gonna
have to suck it up

20:09.942 --> 20:12.979
and pretty much give her away
to someone else.

20:15.548 --> 20:17.016
I'm really sorry.

20:17.049 --> 20:19.652
It's so strange
that the one person

20:19.686 --> 20:22.455
that I'm genuinely so happy
to be with,

20:22.489 --> 20:25.825
I have to hide, like it's, like,
this shameful act.

20:25.858 --> 20:27.460
Mm.

20:27.494 --> 20:30.263
The day she gets married,
I should be set free...

20:30.297 --> 20:31.364
Mm-hmm.

20:31.398 --> 20:32.599
Ugh...

20:32.632 --> 20:34.767
A very twisted way.

20:34.801 --> 20:36.336
[ Sighs ]

20:36.369 --> 20:38.605
Page: For many lesbian
and bisexual women,

20:38.638 --> 20:40.373
being with a chosen partner

20:40.407 --> 20:42.975
can mean leaving their family
and losing their home.

20:43.009 --> 20:46.413
And often, the legal stigma
against homosexuality

20:46.446 --> 20:50.016
dissuades women from reaching
out for government support.

20:50.049 --> 20:53.853
But there are some organizations
that can help.

20:53.886 --> 20:57.557
The LGBTQ collective Umang
harbors women on the run.

20:59.759 --> 21:02.962
Currently, we're in a safe house
at an undisclosed location

21:02.995 --> 21:04.631
to meet
with a lesbian couple

21:04.664 --> 21:06.533
that has recently
fled their village.

21:06.566 --> 21:08.735
Uh, we're gonna interview them
anonymously,

21:08.768 --> 21:11.037
and they're gonna share
their story with us.

21:33.860 --> 21:35.328
I know you've been dealing

21:35.362 --> 21:37.330
with a really difficult
experience,

21:37.364 --> 21:40.867
so thank you
for sharing your story.

21:40.900 --> 21:42.702
Um...

21:42.735 --> 21:44.937
Daniel: Can you tell us what
it was like to be at home,

21:44.971 --> 21:46.873
even before you two met
and what it's like --

21:46.906 --> 21:48.508
Once you expressed that
you were in love,

21:48.541 --> 21:49.776
how that changed?

22:31.684 --> 22:33.620
When you have
such a strong connection,

22:33.653 --> 22:34.921
and you are so in love,

22:34.954 --> 22:36.423
and your family's trying
to rip you apart,

22:36.456 --> 22:38.024
what does it feel like, then,

22:38.057 --> 22:40.359
to be separate
from one another?

22:56.042 --> 22:58.511
So, what is that like
then, to --

22:58.545 --> 23:02.114
to be together now, but to have
to be in hiding, and...?

23:23.936 --> 23:26.973
Is there anything that you would
like to say to your family

23:27.006 --> 23:28.741
or to anyone else
out there

23:28.775 --> 23:30.743
that refuses
to accept your love?

23:47.627 --> 23:49.829
Page: You look at the reality

23:49.862 --> 23:53.766
of what's potentially
the majority of queer women

23:53.800 --> 23:55.935
in this country, and it's --

23:55.968 --> 23:59.138
makes me feel
unbearable sadness.

23:59.171 --> 24:01.974
[ Sighs ]

24:02.008 --> 24:04.744
I think that's something that
I've been thinking about a lot,

24:04.777 --> 24:08.948
and what it means for a woman
to be in the world

24:08.981 --> 24:13.620
and how unbelievably fortunate
I am to have the life

24:13.653 --> 24:15.555
and the freedoms and the control
that I have

24:15.588 --> 24:17.857
that I think we truly take
for granted,

24:17.890 --> 24:19.626
I take for granted, for sure.

24:24.631 --> 24:25.632
Inhale!

24:25.665 --> 24:27.166
[ All inhale sharply ]

24:27.199 --> 24:29.636
Exhaling.

24:29.669 --> 24:32.171
Breathe -- help to change
your emotions.

24:32.204 --> 24:34.774
Breathe -- help
to change our thoughts.

24:34.807 --> 24:36.909
Inhale, center.
Right side.

24:36.943 --> 24:38.778
[ Inhales sharply ]

24:38.811 --> 24:40.146
Guys, not like that.
Relax, relax!

24:40.179 --> 24:42.281
[ Breathing rapidly ]
Not like --

24:42.314 --> 24:43.950
Just smiling face.
[ Inhales sharply ]

24:43.983 --> 24:46.218
Like that --
is making the good energy.

24:46.252 --> 24:49.722
Page: India has given the world
yoga, a spiritual philosophy

24:49.756 --> 24:52.925
born from religions that
traditionally preach inclusively

24:52.959 --> 24:56.529
and tolerance, so it's the last
place we'd expect to find

24:56.563 --> 24:59.098
a rejection of gender
and sexual fluidity.

24:59.131 --> 25:02.034
And yet, one of India's
most famous gurus

25:02.068 --> 25:05.605
claims that the practice
can cure homosexuality.

25:05.638 --> 25:10.810
So, Ian and I are going on a
pilgrimage to yoga our day away.

25:20.887 --> 25:25.191
After hours of travel,
we finally arrive in Haridwar,

25:25.224 --> 25:27.694
an ancient city on the banks

25:27.727 --> 25:30.697
of the mythologized
Ganges river.

25:30.730 --> 25:32.298
It is the sacred space and home
to Baba Ramdev,

25:32.331 --> 25:34.767
the celebrity Hindu swami.

25:37.770 --> 25:42.008
Ramdev leads yoga every morning
on his daily TV show,

25:42.041 --> 25:46.312
exposure which must help promote
his flagship ashram.

25:46.345 --> 25:50.617
His brand has even expanded to
include a popular product line

25:50.650 --> 25:54.220
of organic convenience foods
and traditional medicines.

25:54.253 --> 25:57.590
But after months of negotiations
to interview Ramdev,

25:57.624 --> 25:59.959
we have no confirmation
he'll meet us.

25:59.992 --> 26:04.230
So, we're visiting one of his
associates Dr. Ajay Magan.

26:04.263 --> 26:07.600
He has arranged for us to get
aura and chakra healing,

26:07.634 --> 26:09.769
which many people seek
as a practice

26:09.802 --> 26:12.204
to cure a wide range of issues
and aliments

26:12.238 --> 26:14.941
but also homosexuality.

26:14.974 --> 26:16.843
I have done a lot of research
on this subject.

26:16.876 --> 26:20.279
So, what I will be showing you,
it has got a scientific base.

26:20.312 --> 26:22.615
What did the test show you,
exactly?

26:22.649 --> 26:23.950
-About your aura.
-Mm.

26:23.983 --> 26:25.985
Like, what's your
biomagnetic field.

26:26.018 --> 26:27.920
-Are you ready for the test?
-Yeah!

26:27.954 --> 26:29.889
-Let's just try it out.
-Yeah, sure.

26:29.922 --> 26:32.258
I'll be checking
your chakras, right?
Okay.

26:32.291 --> 26:34.126
You have to step forward,
please.

26:34.160 --> 26:36.829
Okay. The shoulder,
the emotional part.

26:36.863 --> 26:40.700
See, this is going clockwise
as well as anticlockwise.

26:40.733 --> 26:43.102
It shows
you feel very troubled.

26:43.135 --> 26:45.204
You're not stable emotionally.

26:45.237 --> 26:47.039
-Correct!
-This is --

26:47.073 --> 26:48.074
[ Laughter ]

26:48.107 --> 26:49.308
This is getting good.

26:50.810 --> 26:52.144
Okay.

26:52.178 --> 26:53.780
Dr. Adavni:
The basic chakra is not fine.

26:53.813 --> 26:55.882
It's not natural, we can say.

26:55.915 --> 26:58.250
-Yeah.
-This is related to sex.

26:58.284 --> 27:00.787
