of your body.

27:11.964 --> 27:14.233
Yeah.
You can be inside.

27:14.266 --> 27:17.369
-Okay.
-Just sit down for a minute.

27:18.805 --> 27:20.673
Daniel: Thank you.

27:20.707 --> 27:22.709
Read me a little bit,
and then...

27:22.742 --> 27:25.211
Yeah.
...let's see if I have
to get in there or not.

27:25.244 --> 27:26.445
One more step...

27:26.478 --> 27:27.780
Daniel: Uh-oh.

27:27.814 --> 27:29.115
It's going inside.

27:29.148 --> 27:30.282
That means your aura
is negative.

27:30.316 --> 27:31.751
Wow.

27:31.784 --> 27:33.052
Dr. Magan: This is
what our science is.

27:33.085 --> 27:34.286
I'm sorry
if I'm offending you.

27:34.320 --> 27:36.222
No, I -- I think
this is right on.

27:36.255 --> 27:39.125
Dr. Magan: I'm taking the
negativity out from the chakras.

27:42.161 --> 27:45.998
From health, wealth,
happiness, and success --

27:46.032 --> 27:47.199
all the negativity
should be gone.

27:47.233 --> 27:48.868
Yeah.

27:48.901 --> 27:50.970
Daniel: So, you've had people
come here that say,

27:51.003 --> 27:53.072
"Hey, I'm -- I'm --
I'm just struggling

27:53.105 --> 27:55.708
with my sexuality," or,
"I have gay tendencies."

27:55.742 --> 27:57.209
You do the healing,
and they've come to you

27:57.243 --> 27:58.911
and told you that
they feel better, or --

27:58.945 --> 28:00.747
Yes, yes!
What are --
What are their results?

28:00.780 --> 28:02.381
Tomorrow you're the one
who'll tell us what is --

28:02.414 --> 28:03.916
-How I feel?
-Well, yes. Absolutely.

28:03.950 --> 28:05.852
Okay.
That's a deal.

28:05.885 --> 28:07.754
-Yes.
-Okay, well...

28:07.787 --> 28:10.256
So nice.
Thank you so much for welc--

28:10.289 --> 28:12.024
welcoming us here, and...

28:12.058 --> 28:13.059
[ Bird squawks ]

28:13.092 --> 28:16.228
[ Speaks native language ]

28:16.262 --> 28:19.799
Page: Though we didn't get
a treatment from Ramdev,

28:19.832 --> 28:21.433
his influence has made him

28:21.467 --> 28:24.170
an increasingly
controversial figure.

28:24.203 --> 28:26.305
While some have likened him
to Gandhi,

28:26.338 --> 28:27.974
others call his claims

28:28.007 --> 28:31.110
that he can cure diseases
like HIV criminal.

28:31.143 --> 28:32.812
[ Horn honks ]

28:32.845 --> 28:35.081
And last night, we were told
Ramdev would meet us,

28:35.114 --> 28:39.018
so we woke up this morning,
still gay,

28:39.051 --> 28:41.020
and headed out to meet
the legend himself.

28:44.390 --> 28:45.892
Daniel: Thank you.

28:45.925 --> 28:48.027
Thank you.
Please sit down.

28:48.060 --> 28:51.163
Thank you so much for
having us here today.

28:51.197 --> 28:53.165
This is your house,
this is where you live.

28:53.199 --> 28:54.200
It's...

28:54.233 --> 28:55.367
Uh...

29:39.378 --> 29:41.080
Maybe you can
tell us more

29:41.113 --> 29:43.415
about your teachings
and your philosophy.

30:03.035 --> 30:06.238
And, uh, do you do work
involving, um, people

30:06.272 --> 30:08.607
who are homosexual
or bisexual,

30:08.640 --> 30:11.010
uh, curative work
for that?

30:31.964 --> 30:34.566
A lot of people, particularly
homosexual people [scoffs]

30:34.600 --> 30:37.036
feel like they're
just, you know,

30:37.069 --> 30:38.637
they're naturally born gay.

30:38.670 --> 30:40.072
And I'm just wondering

30:40.106 --> 30:41.140
what you would say
to those people.

30:57.990 --> 31:01.460
The issue with that is that
people, for some reason,

31:01.493 --> 31:03.562
believe that it's an illness
that can be cured.

31:03.595 --> 31:06.498
So it seems like people
coming here with that in mind

31:06.532 --> 31:08.968
are spending money and going
through these things

31:09.001 --> 31:11.003
and it actually
isn't going to help them.

31:11.037 --> 31:14.206
So, it -- I just wonder
how you feel about that.

31:49.075 --> 31:52.378
Page: Ramdev's claims seem
to oppose the philosophies

31:52.411 --> 31:53.679
he himself believes.

31:53.712 --> 31:55.681
With the attention
of the nation,

31:55.714 --> 31:57.249
we can't help but imagine

31:57.283 --> 32:00.086
the impact he'd make
preaching acceptance.

32:10.729 --> 32:14.033
[ Speaks native language ]

32:14.066 --> 32:16.635
Very good. Very good.
Very good.

32:16.668 --> 32:18.070
Very good.

32:21.040 --> 32:24.310
Page: We're back in Mumbai,
in a Bollywood recording studio,

32:24.343 --> 32:28.981
to meet the Six Pack Band --
India's latest pop sensation.

32:29.015 --> 32:30.449
[ Pop music playing ]

32:30.482 --> 32:32.251
[ Band singing
in native language ]

32:52.471 --> 32:54.640
Page: With millions of views
on YouTube,

32:54.673 --> 32:58.010
the band has gained attention,
in part because their members

32:58.044 --> 33:01.647
are neither male nor female
but a third gender.

33:01.680 --> 33:05.517
Their singles describe
the struggles that they face

33:05.551 --> 33:10.056
on a daily basis -- being part
of India's hijra community.

33:12.424 --> 33:15.361
Hijra's are considered
one of the oldest recorded

33:15.394 --> 33:17.663
third-gender communities
in the world,

33:17.696 --> 33:21.767
dating back to Hindu scriptures.

33:21.800 --> 33:25.271
And yet, today,
they are often relegated

33:25.304 --> 33:28.574
to the fringes of society
with little options for work.

33:28.607 --> 33:31.077
[ Goats bleating ]

33:31.110 --> 33:32.244
-Hey.
-Hi.

33:32.278 --> 33:33.645
-Hello.
-I'm Ellen.

33:33.679 --> 33:36.348
Page: Komal,
one of the band members,

33:36.382 --> 33:38.050
has invited us to her home

33:38.084 --> 33:40.386
where she lives
in a hijra community.

33:56.402 --> 33:57.736
-Thank you, thank you.
-That would be great.

34:03.342 --> 34:05.544
[ Goats bleat ]

34:05.577 --> 34:07.113
Come.

34:07.146 --> 34:09.748
Okay, you go first.

34:10.782 --> 34:12.751
[ Chuckling ]
I'll be right in.

34:12.784 --> 34:14.653
-Beautiful.
-Thank you.

34:14.686 --> 34:16.688
-This is amazing.
-Thanks.

34:16.722 --> 34:18.757
[ Laughs ]
This is not working.

34:24.696 --> 34:26.532
Has everyone lived here
for a long time?

34:42.914 --> 34:45.451
I was wondering if maybe you
could talk about

34:45.484 --> 34:47.519
just the history of those,
in India,

34:47.553 --> 34:50.256
who don't, you know,
conform to, uh,

34:50.289 --> 34:53.525
a specific gender -- identify
with male or female --

34:53.559 --> 34:56.495
and, uh, and what that means
in Indian culture?

34:56.528 --> 34:58.830
And if it's --
if it's changed over time?

35:31.197 --> 35:33.699
Why do you think people
treat you with disrespect?

36:09.735 --> 36:13.572
And how does hijra fit in
to the LGBT community in India

36:13.605 --> 36:16.408
and -- and --
and the current movement

36:16.442 --> 36:18.477
for equality and acceptance?

36:39.865 --> 36:41.833
Although deeply marginalized,

36:41.867 --> 36:45.737
hijras are accepted as part
of India's national identity

36:45.771 --> 36:48.907
and are legally recognized
as a third gender.

36:48.940 --> 36:51.277
Despite this legal
acknowledgement,

36:51.310 --> 36:53.612
there isn't the same
cultural acceptance

36:53.645 --> 36:55.414
for those who are transgender.

36:55.447 --> 36:59.351
But there are some trans people
who are speaking out.

36:59.385 --> 37:02.454
And one of them is
an aspiring Bollywood dancer.

37:02.488 --> 37:05.023
We've traveled to Delhi
to meet with Rajat --

37:05.056 --> 37:07.426
a trans man
and his wife, Lakshmi --

37:07.459 --> 37:10.329
to hear their story
and to pick up a few moves.

37:10.362 --> 37:11.930
I think we just go in.

37:11.963 --> 37:13.965
[ Dog barking frantically ]

37:13.999 --> 37:16.034
-Oh.
-[ Barks ]

37:16.067 --> 37:17.903
-Whoa.
-Hi.

37:17.936 --> 37:20.872
Page: The couple recently
had to leave their hometown

37:20.906 --> 37:23.442
and are starting a new life
together here.

37:23.475 --> 37:24.910
I'm Ellen.
-Please go in now.

37:24.943 --> 37:26.778
-Nice to meet you.
-How's it going?

37:26.812 --> 37:28.514
My dancing consists
of, like, this...

37:28.547 --> 37:29.781
-She's like...
-So, yeah.

37:29.815 --> 37:31.650
...like, a grandpa dance.
-That's about it.

37:31.683 --> 37:34.453
-1, 2, 3. 1, 2, 3.
-Oh, I like that.

37:34.486 --> 37:36.588
[ All chanting 1, 2, 3 ]

37:42.528 --> 37:43.762
Yeah, wow.

37:43.795 --> 37:44.996
This is harder
than it looks, huh?

37:51.403 --> 37:52.571
Daniel: Yeah?

37:53.839 --> 37:55.273
That's your...
That's your dream?

38:06.952 --> 38:08.687
What was it like
growing up for you

38:08.720 --> 38:10.456
and grappling
with your identity?

38:39.050 --> 38:40.051
Wow.

38:40.085 --> 38:41.353
What was the injection?

38:43.689 --> 38:44.990
-For what?
-To make you go unconscious?

38:45.023 --> 38:46.392
Rajat: Unconscious, yeah.

38:59.871 --> 39:00.906
How long were you
in the hospital?

39:12.518 --> 39:14.520
How long were you locked --
locked inside?

39:40.546 --> 39:43.582
Page: We're in Delhi meeting
with Rajat --

39:43.615 --> 39:46.151
a trans man
and his wife, Lakshmi --

39:46.184 --> 39:48.787
who recently fled
from their hometown.

39:48.820 --> 39:50.522
How much are you in contact
with your family?

39:53.058 --> 39:54.526
You don't talk to them?

40:12.210 --> 40:13.645
Daniel:
Your mom lied and said

40:13.679 --> 40:15.847
she was in the --
in the emergency room?

40:28.860 --> 40:30.496
They do the chakra work,

40:30.529 --> 40:32.731
they do the --
to like align you.

40:32.764 --> 40:34.099
Rajat:
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

40:58.757 --> 41:00.892
Like kill, legitimately or are
you using that as like a --

41:00.926 --> 41:02.193
I mean, do you really --

41:02.227 --> 41:04.663
you felt like they would
actually harm you?

41:24.916 --> 41:26.251
I have to say, like --

41:26.284 --> 41:28.920
I know you're feeling
the same exact way,

41:28.954 --> 41:32.090
but I think it's such a perfect
example of what love

41:32.123 --> 41:34.125
and that connection to love
can actually do.

41:34.159 --> 41:35.594
Because you're just so committed
to one another.

41:35.627 --> 41:36.995
Yeah.

41:37.028 --> 41:39.565
I'm blown away by your
resilience and your bravery.

41:39.598 --> 41:43.201
Um, but I wonder if you want
to say something right now.

41:43.234 --> 41:45.737
Like do you want to say
something directly

41:45.771 --> 41:47.739
to those in situations
like yours?

41:47.773 --> 41:49.240
'Cause I know just sharing
your story's

41:49.274 --> 41:50.709
gonna mean so much
to people.

42:17.636 --> 42:19.638
It's so beautiful
you have one another.

42:19.671 --> 42:21.106
You're very fortunate.
Yeah.

42:21.139 --> 42:22.240
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah.

42:26.077 --> 42:27.679
Page: In Indian philosophy,

42:27.713 --> 42:30.048
one of the four aims of life
is moksha --

42:30.081 --> 42:32.283
spiritual liberation --

42:32.317 --> 42:37.322
the transcendent state attained
by finding your inner wisdom,

42:37.355 --> 42:38.990
your true essence

42:39.024 --> 42:42.093
stripped of societal
expectations.

42:46.064 --> 42:49.735
Throughout our journey,
we've heard many stories

42:49.768 --> 42:53.071
about the challenges
of being LGBTQ in India.

42:53.104 --> 42:57.342
But we see that at its core,
India's culture is rooted

42:57.375 --> 43:01.312
in traditions and rituals that
hold a spirit of acceptance

43:01.346 --> 43:04.182
and a celebration of diversity.

43:09.655 --> 43:12.724
We often look outward
to bring progress.

43:12.758 --> 43:14.660
But in the case of India,

43:14.693 --> 43:18.029
progress may come
from looking within,

43:18.063 --> 43:21.066
to the wisdom their philosophies
already hold.

43:25.971 --> 43:27.272
[ Horn honks ]

43:27.305 --> 43:29.407
Daniel: Aw, this honking
is out of control.

43:29.440 --> 43:31.309
Can we just,
like, honk slightly?

43:31.342 --> 43:33.679
Not so forcefully
every once in a while?

43:33.712 --> 43:36.047
Okay, before we came --
'cause Ellen's been here before

43:36.081 --> 43:38.183
and she -- she was,
like, you know, get ready,

43:38.216 --> 43:39.918
there's gonna be
a lot of honking,

43:39.951 --> 43:41.720
as if that's, like,
gonna destroy me.

43:41.753 --> 43:44.022
I am kind of sensitive to sound,
to be quite honest.

43:44.055 --> 43:45.791
And I will say that

43:45.824 --> 43:49.127
there is a symphony
of honking going on

43:49.160 --> 43:52.030
at all times of the day
and into the night.

43:52.063 --> 43:53.965
Yo, listen, the traffic's
pretty damn crazy.

43:53.999 --> 43:56.334
I just go along for the ride,
if you know what I'm saying?

43:56.367 --> 44:00.271
[ Horns honking ]
